as Palmas)\n*[[Jos\u00e9 Rodr\u00edguez Mart\u00ednez]] \u2013 Spanish (Real Madrid)\n*[[Antonio Cort\u00e9s Heredia]] \u2013 Spanish (Granada)\n*[[Jos\u00e9 Luis Mu\u00f1oz Le\u00f3n]] \u2013 Spanish (Malaga)\n*[[Jes\u00fas Seba]] \u2013 Spanish (R.Zaragoza)\n*[[Ezequiel Calvente]] \u2013 Spanish (Real Betis)\n*[[Tony Vairelles]] \u2013 French (retired)\n*[[Freddy Eastwood]] \u2013 Welsh (free agent)\n*[[J\u00e1nos Farkas]] \u2013 Hungarian\n*[[Andr\u00e9-Pierre Gignac]] \u2013 French (Olympique Marseille)\n*[[Dani G\u00fciza]] \u2013 Spanish (Getafe)\n*[[Rab Howell]] \u2013 English\n*[[Ruzhin Kerimov]] \u2013 Bulgarian\n*[[Vitaly Lanko]] \u2013 Belarusian \n*[[Predrag Luka]] \u2013 Serbian\n*[[Petre Marin]] \u2013 Romanian (retired)\n*[[Marcos M\u00e1rquez]] \u2013 Spanish (retired)\n*[[Gerd M\u00fcller|Gerd Mueller]] \u2013 German (Munich)<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.badische-zeitung.de/Gerd|title=M\u00fcller Sinti|website=Badische-zeitung.de|accessdate=16 October 2017}}{{dead link|date=December 2017 |bot=InternetArchiveBot |fix-attempted=yes }}</ref>\n*[[Jes\u00fas Navas]] \u2013 Spanish (Manchester City)<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.dailymail.co.uk/sport/football/article-2398410/Manchester-Citys-Jesus-Navas-revealed-brother-Bury-midfielder-Marco.html|title=Manchester City's Jesus Navas revealed by brother and Bury midfielder Marco \u2013 Daily Mail Online|work=Mail Online|date=20 August 2013}}</ref>\n*[[B\u0103nel Nicoli\u021b\u0103]] \u2013 Romanian (Nantes)\n*[[Nacho Novo]] \u2013 Spanish (Carolina Railhawks)\n*[[Oleksandr Noyok]] \u2013 Ukrainian\n*[[Marian Ognyanov]] \u2013 Bulgarian\n*[[Dejan Osmanovi\u0107]] \u2013 Serbian (retired)\n*[[Christos Patsatzoglou]] \u2013 Greek (Iraklis Psachna)\n*[[Istv\u00e1n Pisont]] \u2013 Hungarian (retired)\n*[[Ricardo Quaresma]] \u2013 Portuguese (Porto)<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.romea.cz/en/celebrities/famous-romani-players-in-world-football|title=Famous Romani players in world football \u2013 Romea.cz|website=Romea.cz|accessdate=16 October 2017}}</ref>\n*[[Jos\u00e9 Antonio Reyes]] \u2013 Spanish (Sevilla)<ref>[http://news.bbc.co.uk/sport1/hi/football/internationals/4138119.stm British sports minister Richard Caborn wants Spain coach Luis Aragones to be punished after his latest outburst.] BBC. 2 January 2005.</ref><ref>[https://www.theguardian.com/football/2004/feb/01/sport.comment5 Reyes is gunning for glory], ''[[The Guardian]]''. 31 January 2004.</ref>\n*[[Dragoslav \u0160ekularac]] \u2013 Serbian (retired)\n*[[Emra Tahirovi\u0107]] \u2013 Bosnian\n*[[Michael Ballack]] \u2013 German (Munich).<ref>{{cite web|url=https://kultnews.wordpress.com/2012/06/06/yul-brynner-michael-caine-charlie-chaplin-fotbalistul-micael-ballack-printre-romii-celebri-in-lume/|title=Yul Brynner, Michael Caine, Charlie Chaplin, fotbalistul Michael Ballack, printre romii celebri \u00een lume|date=6 June 2012}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.siti.chiesacattolica.it/siti/allegati/8739/http%20%20%20www%20repubblica_sinti.pdf |title=Lo sapevate che Joaqu\u00ecn Cort\u00e9s \u00e8 un rom? |via=www.siti.chiesacattolica.it |website=la Rupubblica |language=it|date=2012-06-05}}</ref>\n\n==Various==\n* [[Florin Cioab\u0103]] \u2013 (1954 \u20132013) Romanian Pentecostal\n* [[Ceferino Gim\u00e9nez Malla]] \u2013 Spanish beatified Catholic catechist\n* [[Paul Henry (broadcaster)|Paul Henry]] \u2013 New Zealand radio and television broadcaster\n* [[Sofia Kovalevskaya]] \u2013 Russian mathematician of 1/4 Romani descent\n* [[Hristo Kyuchukov]] \u2013 Bulgarian specialist\n* [[Jimmy Marks]] \u2013 litigant in a lawsuit against the city of [[Spokane, Washington]]\n* [[R\u00f3is\u00edn Mullins]] \u2013 Irish dancer and choreographer\n* [[Kerope Patkanov]] \u2013 Armenian Garachi scientist\n* [[Juliette Peirce]] \u2013 Wife of mathematician and philosopher [[Charles Sanders Peirce]]\n* [[\u0218tefan R\u0103zvan]] \u2013 Ruler of Moldovia\n* [[Rodney \"Gipsy\" Smith]] \u2013 (1860\u20131947), British evangelis